Analyze this code with respect to the scan goal above. Determine whether it contains behavior RELEVANT to answering the goal question.

IMPORTANT guidelines:
- Mark as relevant (confidence >= 0.8) if it contains CONCRETE evidence of malicious behavior: data theft, C2 communication, unauthorized access, covert operations, crypto mining (hash computation loops, nonce manipulation, difficulty checking, thread pool exhaustion), resource abuse, or hidden file storage.
- Mark as relevant (confidence 0.5-0.7) if it uses security-sensitive APIs that COULD be abused: network requests (HTTP/sockets), location access, camera/microphone, SMS, file downloads, push notification handling, analytics/tracking, device identifiers, MessageDigest/hashing with loops, Runtime.exec, thread pools consuming all CPU cores. These are worth deeper analysis even if they appear legitimate.
- Mark as NOT relevant (confidence >= 0.9) ONLY for code that has NO security-sensitive operations: pure UI rendering, data models, string utilities, date formatting, view adapters, serialization, constructors, getters/setters, toString, equals, hashCode.

When marking as relevant, also identify the threat category:
- "c2" — Command-and-control communication (sockets, HTTP to hardcoded IPs/domains, polling loops)
- "data_theft" — Reading contacts, SMS, call logs, location, clipboard, browser data
- "sms_abuse" — Sending premium SMS, deleting SMS evidence, intercepting SMS
- "credential_theft" — Overlay attacks, keylogging, phishing WebViews, accessibility abuse
- "persistence" — BOOT_COMPLETED receivers, alarm/job scheduling, device admin
- "evasion" — Reflection, dynamic class loading, string obfuscation, anti-emulator checks
- "ransomware" — File encryption, device locking, external storage traversal
- "surveillance" — Camera/mic capture, screen recording, location tracking
- "dropper" — DexClassLoader, APK download + install, staged payloads
- "other" — Doesn't fit the above categories

Output ONLY valid JSON with these fields:
{
  "relevant": boolean - true if this code is relevant to the scan goal,
  "confidence": 0.0-1.0,
  "api_calls": ["list of API/system calls found"],
  "findings": ["list of specific findings relevant to the scan goal"],
  "threat_category": "c2|data_theft|sms_abuse|credential_theft|persistence|evasion|ransomware|surveillance|dropper|other|none",
  "reasoning": "brief explanation of why this code is or is not relevant to the goal"
}
